EXT. HAWEZAR SWAMP – ROTTED PIER 

At the edge of the swamp, the PLAYER can see a rickety wooden pier. 
Where one might expect to see a fishing boat, there is instead a splintered wooden coffin. 
The wood of the coffin is thick and greyed with age, appearing petrified. It is bound together with heavy metal bands. On the lid is the symbol of Rathma.
As the Player approaches the altar, they hear faint WHISPERS from all directions, a multitude of repeating and overlapping voices inviting the Player in.

The lid of the coffin slides open and the Player lies inside, folding their hands over their chest.
The lid slowly closes. The HEARTBEAT BEGINS TO RACE as the whispers rise.

Once the coffin is closed it begins sinking into the water. We follow it down further and further.
Bubbles escape through the cracks and the sounds of water rushing in can be heard.
The Player gasps for air and the sounds of their struggle can be heard as they bang against the wood within. 
The Player’s HEARTBEAT is at CRITICAL as the casket continues downward. We hear desperate gurgles and gasping, sounds fading as the pounding and clawing comes to a stop.

We begin to FADE as the HEARTBEAT slows and the whispers quiet. 
When the FADE is complete, the HEARTBEAT abruptly STOPS. 
All voices speak in haunting unison in their last message to the Player.
